      "message": "Abandoned\n\n> There can be up to 2000 stripes on a file,\n\nThanks for that - I did wonder.  The Linux client use calloc() here so I wrote this patch, but wasn't really confident.  I'll fix up the linux client to use a more appropriate allocation.",
